Simon: Simon Tseko Nkoli was an anti-apartheid student activist and one of the founders of the black gay movement. Performed by dancer and choreographer Thami Tshabalala, Simon pays homage to Nkoli while detailing the fruitful journey of his struggles and triumphs.
